{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1474277648,"nonce":"RGbRM14fhy39Oy4pthsWPfkPX8g=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI0Nzk0ODczMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/947#issuecomment-247948732"},"message":"\u003e I would prefer not rush with this. Yes, tool_dependencies.xml has issues but so has conda (e.g. conda/conda-build#877).\n\nThis issue is going away soon, and once this is the case we should choose a relatively long path in planemo to test tools, so that we are sure that all underlying dependencies have been rebuilt.\n\n\u003e I would be happiest to have some kind of transition/bug-report period before permanently migrating to conda. I would not be surprised if there are still galaxy instances around that are not having conda up and running (as mentioned by @natefoo).\n\nExisting revisions will not be changed, and in other areas we are also advancing new features, like metadata column headers, tool profiles and so on. It has to be done at some point, so why not now? A significant fraction of instances that haven't updated until now will probably not have been updated in the next 6 months either, and I would guess that these instances will also be slow with updating their installed tools. But I agree, as long as the current tool_dependencies.xml has no issues, we should probably at least wait until 16.10 before we update tools just to get rid of the toolshed dependencies.","files":null}]}